" I've tried various solutions (including plugins) to keep VIM functioning normally with
" all " keyboard layouts. The best option (unfortunately) is generating keymaps and
" including it in ~/.vimrc.
" Pros: intuitive solution, easy to use, no plugins required
" Cons: Searching (with / or ?) requires either rebinding "ю" key on a system
" level or keeping the current keyboard layout in mind.

